__DESCRIPTION__

plenv is yet another Perl5 environment manager, it's inspired from ruby's rbenv.

plenv is a tools for managing multiple version of Perl installers on one computer.

It is a competitor of perlbrew, but implemented as a Bash script.
It also allows you to override the Perl version with an environment variable.

plenv is ...
* very fast at (ba|z)shrc
* switch perl5 version per project, very easily

* [Source](https://github.com/tokuhirom/plenv)
* [about plenv](http://blog.64p.org/entry/2013/01/21/134639)

